Load the plyr library, sum the number of departures and arrivals from the routes data frame by their source/destination airport ID. Rename these and column names as flights Join the new datasets (i.e. departures and arrivals) into the airports data frame (create two separate dataframes, one for arrivals and one for departures)

library(plyr)
departures <- ddply(routes, .(sourceAirportID), "nrow")
names(departures)[2] <- "flights"

arrivals <- ddply(routes, .(destinationAirportID), "nrow")
names(arrivals)[2] <- "flights"

airportDest <- merge(airports, departures, by.x = "ID", by.y = "sourceAirportID")
airportAriv <- merge(airports, arrivals, by.x = "ID", by.y = "destinationAirportID")

Let’s create a blank slate we will use later on This layer will be added to any map later on so that we will clear all unecessary background objects

blank_slate <- 
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), 
        panel.background = element_rect(fill = 'white', colour = 'white'), 
        axis.line = element_line(colour = "white"), legend.position="none",
        axis.ticks=element_blank(), axis.text.x=element_blank(),
        axis.text.y=element_blank())

Create a foundation layer upon which we will plot our maps unto Note: the contents are empty

my_base <- ggplot() + coord_fixed() +
  xlab("") + ylab("")

Add map to our_world plot to the foundation layer (my_base) Take note: x=long and y=lat

world_plot <- my_base + geom_polygon(data=our_world, aes(x=long, y=lat, group=group), 
                                     colour="light green", fill="light green")


world_plot

Let’s add data points from the airportAriv to world_plot map

  world_plot +
  geom_point(data=airportAriv, 
             aes(x=lon, y=lat), colour="Navy Blue", 
             fill="Pink",pch=21, size=5, alpha=I(0.7))

Now let’s make the data point locations correspond with their real values (flights)

  world_plot +
  geom_point(data=airportAriv, 
             aes(x=lon, y=lat, size=flights), colour="Navy Blue", 
             fill="Pink",pch=21, alpha=I(0.7))

Remember our Russia dataset, let’s plot all airports in Russia

ru_basic <- my_base + geom_polygon(data=Russia, aes(x=long, y=lat, group=group), 
                                           colour="light green", fill="light green")

create a data frame from the airportAriv data frame where the country is Russia and plot the arrival flights

ru_air_ariv = subset(airportAriv, airportAriv$country=="Russia")

ru_maper <- 
  ru_basic +
  geom_point(data=ru_air_ariv, 
             aes(x=lon, y=lat, size=flights), colour="Blue", 
             fill="Yellow",pch=21, alpha=I(0.7))

Let’s plot the previous map but this time we will include the blank layer (blank_slate) Also, using the geom_text() function, we will plot the cities as well.

ru_maper +blank_slate

ru_maper +blank_slate +
  geom_text(data=ru_air_ariv, aes(lon, lat, label = city), size=2)
